verbose_text: In summary, Ang-(1-7) protects H9c2 cardiomyoblasts against HG induced cytotoxicity, cell apoptosis, oxidative stress, mitochondrial damage and inflammation, and PI3K / Akt signaling pathway activation may play a key role in the protective function of Ang-(1-7).
evidence: H9c2 cardiomyoblasts against HG-induced cytotoxicity, cell apoptosis, oxidative stress, mitochondrial damage and inflammation
